This paper deals with zero-shot learning (ZSL) in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attribute-class mapping, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) for tasks such as text classification. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on standard benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
